values:
a radio with guts


it was on the 2nd floor on coronado street

i used to get drunk

and throw the radio through the window

while it was playing, and, of course,

it would break the glass in the window

and the radio would sit there on the roof

still playing

and i'd tell my woman,

"Ah, what a marvelous radio!"

the next morning i'd take the window

off the hinges

and carry it down the street

to the glass man

who would put in another pane.

i kept throwing that radio through the window

each time i got drunk

and it would sit there on the roof

still playing-

a magic radio

a radio with guts,

and each morning i'd take the window 

back to the glass man.

i don't remember how it ended exactly

though i do remember

we finally moved out.

there was a woman downstairs who worked in

the garden in her bathing suit,

she really dug with that trowel

and she put her behind up in the air

and i used to sit in the window

and watch the sun shine all over that thing

while the music played.

April
  	
  	If you had come away with me
into another state
we had been quiet together.
But there the sun coming up
out of the nothing beyond the lake was
too low in the sky,
there was too great a pushing
against him,
too much of sumac buds, pink
in the head
with the clear gum upon them,
too many opening hearts of lilac leaves,
too many, too many swollen
limp poplar tassels on the
bare branches!
It was too strong in the air.
I had no rest against that
springtime!
The pounding of the hoofs on the
raw sods
stayed with me half through the night.
I awoke smiling but tired.

William Carlos Williams

Always Marry An April Girl
  	
Praise the spells and bless the charms,
I found April in my arms.
April golden, April cloudy,
Gracious, cruel, tender, rowdy;
April soft in flowered languor,
April cold with sudden anger,
Ever changing, ever true --
I love April, I love you.

Ogden Nash

So my sister recently pointed out my obsession with mellow music.  At first I laughed it off and denied it.  But the more I think about it, the more I realize how much mellow and slow paced music I listen to.  Elliot and Sufjan to name a few.  And it's weird that I listen to such mellow music because often I am a very hyperactive person.  often annoyingly hyperactive.

Maybe I like mellow music so much because it comforts me.  You see, I'm often very uncomfortable when I'm feeling hyperactive.  I wish I could calm down, but I can't.  being hyperactive makes me seem much less mature than I think I really am.  I guess mellow music just soothes my spirit.

hmmm...

the wonderful thing about life and the guitar is that there's always something left to be discovered.  a new chord, or a new riff, or if you put the capo on it changes everything.  there's a wonderful connection there.  this year, lit and art history ( yes, you heard me right) have made me constantly look for symbols and metaphors.  this year has completely changed how i see things.  it's like ive got a new pair of eyes and ears.

So it appears that i haven't written in a while.  Well since my last entry I've turned 18 and entered into my life as an adult.  It's pretty exciting. and yes, i've done all the essential "I just turned 18" errands-- Susie and Sam will vouch for me.  Thank god midterms are over-- I'm officially a second semester senior, although I still have a ton of art history work not to do.  art history sucks, by the way.  juniors, hear me now--DO NOT TAKE ART HISTORY.

Maybe I should start appreciating the happiness.  And it's not like I ever really have a legitimate reason for ever being sad.  maybe the things is, that I'm  happy when I'm sad.  maybe I should finish the fucking paper and not write in this at midnight.

As well as this year has been going in pretty much all aspects of my life, I can't help but feeling somewhat lost and bored.  I feel quite directionless.  I feel like i've been stuck on the same track for 4 years.  Nothing has really changed.  Sure there have been a few minor adjustments here and there, but really what the hell is going on in this town?  Absolutely nothing.  Even the exciting stories that people tell on the weekend that I may or may not have been a part of, are really nothing.  I'm not unhappy or sad, I'm just tired ans ready for something new.  Though I must say, this year has alot in store for me--Biloxi, Paris, Italy, Graduation, etc.  So hopefully those good things on the horizon approach quicker than I expect them to.

A better man would write an entry somehow recapping his feelings about the past year.  i'll just leave you with some lyrics.

" When you first arrive in a new city, nothing makes sense. Everythings unknown, virgin... After you've lived here, walked these streets, you'll know them inside out. You'll know these people.
